description: Prevent boilerplate AI attribution text in commits or PRs
alwaysApply: true
---

# No boilerplate AI attribution text

- Do not add boilerplate AI attribution phrases in commit messages, pull request titles, pull request bodies, or repository files unless explicitly requested by the user.
- Do not add attribution trailers like `Made-with: Cursor` (or similar variants) to commit messages unless explicitly requested by the user.
- Keep commit and PR descriptions focused on the actual technical changes and rationale.
